  "severity": "medium",
  "description": "A flaw was found in the KVM's Intel nested virtualization feature (nVMX). Since L1 and L2 shared branch prediction modes (guest-user and guest-kernel), KVM did not protect indirect branches in L1 from actions in L2. This flaw could lead to code execution on an indirect branch on the host machine.",
